  "For decades Teh Hong Piow chaired Malaysian banking behemoth Public Bank, which he started in 1966.",
  "He officially retired from Public Bank as non-executive chairman on Jan. 1, 2019. Deputy chairman Lai Wan took over as chairman.",
  "In addition to Malaysians, the bank serves millions of customers across Hong Kong, China, Cambodia, Vietnam, Laos and Sri Lanka.",
  "Teh still has substantial stakes in the bank as well as in the listed insurance business, LPI Capital."
